          {
            "bulletPoint": "Christmas Lights Installation, Maintenance, and Removal",
            "description": {
              "en": "Install Christmas lights in Broseley Town annually, including specific installations: 23 sets of pea lights in the memorial garden, 1 set of lights on the fir tree in the memorial garden, 1 set of pea lights on the tree on the square, features to poles in the memorial garden, a 'welcome to Broseley' sign across the high street, festoons on Harwood's building and the butcher's shop, string lights from church street to the social club, and 2 snow fall column motifs. Maintain the lights throughout the installation period with two scheduled run-throughs to check functionality and attend to minor faults. Dismantle and remove all lights after the festival period, as soon as possible after 6 January but no later than 12 January each year. The contractor must be present on Saturday 28 November 2026 to manually switch on the lights after a countdown, and after switch-on, set automatic timers: on at 4pm, off at 10pm weekdays, and 4pm to 11pm weekends. Provide the cost of all-inclusive call outs during the festival period for lights erected and maintenance checks, with call out within 24 hours for major faults including complete motif or light string failure, vandalism, storms, or road traffic accident. Additional call out charges must be stated on the schedule."
            },
