            "description": {
              "en": "Test the Christmas lights to ensure they are safe and functional, including electric testing of all lights to current standards, testing of all electric feeder pillars, and checking all anchor points. All lights and features must be fully functioning prior to installation. Test lights and features during downtime and undertake minor work such as replacing bulbs and fixing faulty connections. Notify BTC immediately of any defective items requiring major repair at additional cost. Erection, testing, and maintenance must be carried out in accordance with the latest Wiring Regulations (BS 7671) by a competent person. Comply with all relevant health and safety legislation and take measures to minimize risk to the public. Produce a Health & Safety Information document including Risk Assessment and Method Statement before installation. Provide General Health & Safety at Work Policy, accreditation certificates, and staff training certificates."
