            "bulletPoint": "Tender Submission Requirements",
            "description": {
              "en": "Submit a price that fits within the budget, offering high quality and value for money. Provide evidence of ability to deliver similar projects to a high quality, satisfactory references, and a copy of the current public liability insurance certificate. The tender must be fully inclusive of all costs, including any costs arising from site visits and access arrangements. All items must be costed individually. Tenders are to be submitted in writing in a sealed marked envelope addressed to the Town Clerk, clearly marked 'Tender'. Provide a copy of the Highway Electrical Registration Scheme certificate, details of proposed LEDs and product warranty information, and any other pertinent documents or certificates. Comply with all written requirements in the tender and with Standing Order 17 and the Bribery Act 2010. No contractor shall contact councillors or staff to encourage or support their tender outside the prescribed process. All tenders will be considered by the Town Council on 9 June 2026 and will receive a response week commencing 15 June 2026."
